{{country data {{{1}}}
| flag link/core
| variant = {{{variant|{{{2|}}}}}}
| size = {{{size|}}}
| name = {{{name|}}}
| altlink = men's national indoor hockey team
| altvar = indoor hockey
| mw = men's
}}<noinclude>{{documentation|content=
==Description==
{{mono|<nowiki>{{idh|nation|variant|size=optional|name=optional}}</nowiki>}}

Produces a flag icon attached to a wikilinked men's national indoor hockey team article.
;Parameters
*''nation'' — Use either the name of the nation or the three-letter country code as used by the [[List of IOC country codes|IOC]]
*''variant'' (optional) — Specifies an alternate (historical) flag to use.  This parameter is documented by the appropriate template in [[:Category:Country data templates]].
*''size'' (optional) — Can be used to change the flag icon size (use sparingly!)
*''name'' (optional) — Can be used to change the wikilink display text

==Examples==
*{{mono|<nowiki>{{idh|Netherlands}}</nowiki>}} → {{idh|Netherlands}}
*{{mono|<nowiki>{{idh|Argentina}}</nowiki>}} → {{idh|Argentina}}
*{{mono|<nowiki>{{idh|ENG}}</nowiki>}} → {{idh|ENG}}
*{{mono|<nowiki>{{idh|AUS}}</nowiki>}} → {{idh|AUS}}
*{{mono|<nowiki>{{idh|Romania|1965}}</nowiki>}} → {{idh|Romania|1965}}
==See also==
*[[Template:Fh]] — for main national field hockey teams
*[[Template:Idhw]] — for women's national age-grade field hockey teams
*[[:Category:European men's national under-21 field hockey teams]]

[[Category:Field hockey templates]]
[[Category:Flag template system]]
}}</noinclude>

